130
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:31,480
Yeah, but I'm just--

131
00:12:31,559 --> 00:12:34,279
I'm sorry about what I said
and how I told you,

132
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:36,639
so forgive me for that.

133
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,519
Okay.

134
00:12:44,639 --> 00:12:48,240
If you need me to forgive you
for something, then sure, I forgive you.

135
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,879
Cool.

136
00:12:53,519 --> 00:12:54,440
Uh, thanks.

137
00:12:58,879 --> 00:12:59,720
Ander…

138
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:05,159
just a reminder, you spent a whole year
tied to a machine, doing chemo.

139
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:10,000
No one should make you feel
like you have to beg or feel guilty

140
00:13:10,519 --> 00:13:11,799
or ask permission.

141
00:13:45,519 --> 00:13:49,559
OMAR, I NEED TO SEE YOU.

142
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:57,000
What's the matter now?

143
00:14:00,399 --> 00:14:02,440
Without you,
I wouldn't have survived cancer.

144
00:14:03,399 --> 00:14:05,600
What you did was incredible, and, um…

145
00:14:07,159 --> 00:14:09,080
I won't ever forget it, but…

146
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:10,799
No, don't say it.

147
00:14:12,159 --> 00:14:13,240
Omar…

148
00:14:14,799 --> 00:14:17,039
maybe the cancer took its toll on us.

149
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,360
Please, no.

150
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,559
Not on me, no.

151
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:23,919
I mean, okay, yes,

152
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,799
I've been in a fucking mental fog,
but I'm not anymore.

153
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:31,320
When I thought about losing you, I--
Listen, uh…

154
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,600
I only love you, Ander.

155
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:35,960
Listen, though.

156
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,960
I'm not talkin' about Patrick now.

157
00:14:40,159 --> 00:14:44,840
I'm… talking about me.
I thought I'd die, but here I am somehow.

158
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,279
I mean, I just wanna live.

159
00:14:47,799 --> 00:14:50,600
There's a ton of things
I still have to do. A ton.

160
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,639
But… you can do them with me.

161
00:15:00,639 --> 00:15:02,440
It's me, dude.

162
00:15:04,279 --> 00:15:05,320
It's Omar.

163
00:15:06,559 --> 00:15:07,679
It's me.

164
00:15:08,279 --> 00:15:10,440
-I know. I know.
-Omar.

165
00:15:10,519 --> 00:15:12,200
And you have to keep being Omar.

166
00:15:12,919 --> 00:15:15,960
But that's why I'm thinking
it's best we end this here

167
00:15:17,279 --> 00:15:20,440
because I don't want this
to become something else entirely.

168
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:35,639
Thank you.

169
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:42,080
Thank you, Omar.
From the bottom of my heart.

170
00:15:43,279 --> 00:15:45,240
And I'm sorry too. I really am.

171
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,480
I was thinkin'
of taking you out to dinner tonight,

172
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,720
so you can clear your head a bit.

173
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,600
You sidetracked me last weekend already.

174
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,639
Rather be at the library
with him on Saturday?

175
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,679
Come to dinner at my place.

176
00:16:21,919 --> 00:16:24,200
We can hang out together a while.

177
00:16:25,639 --> 00:16:26,679
With your dad?

178
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,039
Not what I had in mind, to be honest.

179
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,840
Yeah, but after that,
everything goes smoothly.

180
00:16:32,919 --> 00:16:34,000
Hmm.

181
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,320
Ari, García's gonna be coming over.

182
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:40,000
That way,
I can go over both of your arguments.

183
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,360
-How's it goin'?
-All good, thanks.

184
00:16:51,799 --> 00:16:53,360
I'm goin' to your place for dinner.

185
00:17:01,399 --> 00:17:03,279
SHARE MY LOCATION

186
00:17:05,119 --> 00:17:07,039
DID YOU BLOCK ME?

187
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,559
What's the matter?

188
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,920
Armando.

189
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:25,880
Wait, what?

190
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:29,680
What the fuck does that asshole want?
We're calling the police now.

191
00:17:29,759 --> 00:17:32,759
Hey, hold up.
Want my family knowing about it?

192
00:17:32,839 --> 00:17:34,359
Oh, so you care about your family now?

193
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:37,039
I mean, yeah,
my family and the entire school

194
00:17:37,119 --> 00:17:38,519
and kinda the whole world.

195
00:17:39,039 --> 00:17:40,920
Just relax, okay?

196
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,000
It's all good.

197
00:17:42,759 --> 00:17:44,200
I can handle this guy.

198
00:17:49,519 --> 00:17:52,880
Do you know that, until the age of three,
all I ate was chocolate?

199
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,279
Oh really?

200
00:17:55,079 --> 00:17:56,640
Psst, hey!

201
00:17:57,680 --> 00:18:01,160
Some dumbass guy sure as hell
isn't gonna spoil our…

202
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:03,039
…chocolate party.

203
00:18:21,119 --> 00:18:22,160
No, Mencía, I said--

204
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:30,440
Sorry, I couldn't resist.
You know I just can't help myself.

205
00:18:32,559 --> 00:18:33,680
Mencía.

206
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,400
-Thanks.
-Samuel?

207
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:12,000
No, I don't want any, thanks.
Gotta stay sharp for tomorrow's debate.

208
00:20:15,039 --> 00:20:16,319
Hmm.

209
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,400
The winner's going
to the European debate competition,

210
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:27,359
where they'll have to present
but have to do it in French, right?

211
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:29,640
Hmm. Well, yes.

212
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,640
What would you do?

213
00:20:32,759 --> 00:20:34,079
Don't you speak French?

214
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,279
I have a decent grasp of it.

215
00:20:40,359 --> 00:20:42,880
Yeah, for a local yokel, maybe.

216
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,319
What?

217
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,880
But don't worry.

218
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:50,400
Because since Ari's gonna win,
that won't be a problem, right?

219
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:52,839
You know, you should thank him, Samuel.

220
00:20:53,839 --> 00:20:54,680
Why?

221
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:59,880
Because people like us rise
to the challenge when we're questioned.

222
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,440
I'm sorry. People like you?

223
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:04,680
Yeah, people who studied on scholarship.

224
00:21:04,759 --> 00:21:05,839
Ah, right.

225
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:08,920
