His mom went as well.

233
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,720
I was told he'd been exonerated, though.

234
00:21:35,799 --> 00:21:38,279
More like he didn't wait
to get the verdict.

235
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:42,359
So you're saying his brother
fled the country while on probation?

236
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,759
Just so you know
the gem of a brother-in-law you'd have.

237
00:21:44,839 --> 00:21:46,559
See you tomorrow.

238
00:22:00,839 --> 00:22:01,799
Mencía!

239
00:22:05,079 --> 00:22:07,400
-What are you doing here?
-I'm trying to have a conversation.

240
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:10,400
-You're following me.
-I saw your Instagram.

241
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:12,880
Mencía, please.

242
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:16,599
